# Detail pages (`src/app/shared/detail`)

Read-only entity detail **pages** for user portal tables. Do not use `DetailModalService` or ad-hoc modal markup.

## Structure

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `detail.types.ts` | `DetailDefinition`, `DetailFieldDef`, `DetailActionDef` |
| `define-detail.ts` | `defineDetail<T>()` |
| `detail-page.constants.ts` | `buildDetailPageActions()`, action id constants |
| `detail-view/` | Renders `DetailDefinition` + entity data |
| `detail-field-renderer/` | Built-in field widgets (text, date, status, route, vehicle, warehouse, translate) |
| `index.ts` | Barrel |

## Layout components

| Component | Path | Role |
|-----------|------|------|
| `DetailPageLayoutComponent` | `shared/ui/detail-page-layout/` | Slots: `[detailBack]`, `app-page-title`, `[detailSummary]`, `[detailContent]`, `[detailFooterActions]`; optional `entityTab` — card accent on summary + detail cards |
| `EntityDetailSummaryComponent` | `shared/ui/entity-detail-summary/` | Primary glance band — **location left**, **status badge right** |
| `DetailActionBarComponent` | `shared/ui/detail-action-bar/` | Header action buttons; `layout: 'inline' \| 'stack'` |

### Summary band (`EntityDetailSummaryComponent`)

- **Transport / freight:** `kind="route"` + `[origin]` + `[destination]` → `RouteDisplayComponent`
- **Warehouse:** `kind="warehouse"` + `[warehouseName]` + `[warehouseCity]` → `WarehouseDisplayComponent`
- **Status:** `[status]` → `StatusBadgeComponent` (only colored pill on the page)
- **All viewports:** location left / status right (single flex row; status `align-self: flex-start` — does **not** stack below location on mobile)
- Project with `detailSummary` attribute into `DetailPageLayoutComponent`

**Do not** duplicate status or location in `*.detail.ts` — they live only in the summary band.

## Navigation helpers (`portal/user/common/entity-detail-navigation.ts`)

| Export | Role |
|--------|------|
| `navigateToEntityDetail(router, detailUrl, origin)` | Table row click / viewDetails — passes `detailOrigin: 'search' \| 'our'` in router state |
| `readEntityDetailOrigin()` | Read `detailOrigin` from `history.state` on detail page load |
| `resolveDetailBack(tab, isOwnListing, origin?)` | Back link URL + `labelKey` (`portal.user.nav.search` or `portal.user.nav.ourListings`) |
| `resolveDetailSubtitleKey(isOwnListing, origin?)` | `portal.user.pages.listingDetail.subtitleSearch` or `.subtitleOur` |
| `isOwnListingEntity(entity, companyId)` | Ownership check for actions + fallbacks |

## Per-entity pattern

1. **Definition** — `detail/<entity>.detail.ts` with `defineDetail<Entity>()({ sections: [...] })` — **no** status, route, or warehouse fields (in summary band).
2. **Page** — `detail/<entity>-detail-page.component.*` loads `getById`, composes layout + summary + `DetailView`.
3. **Table pages** — `[rowClickEnabled]="true"` + `(rowClick)` + `viewDetails` action → `navigateToEntityDetail()`.

## Routes + URLs

Detail routes in `user.routes.ts` (after `create` and `:id/edit`):

- `transport/:id` → `TransportDetailPageComponent`
- `freight/:id` → `FreightDetailPageComponent`
- `warehouse/:id` → `WarehouseDetailPageComponent`

URL builders in `user-urls.ts`: `userTransportDetailUrl(id)`, `userFreightDetailUrl(id)`, `userWarehouseDetailUrl(id)`.

## Page header

- **Title:** static `portal.user.pages.view*.title`
- **Subtitle:** static UX copy — **never** entity data (no `origin → destination`, no warehouse name). Use computed `pageSubtitleKey()` from `resolveDetailSubtitleKey()` → `portal.user.pages.listingDetail.subtitleSearch` / `.subtitleOur` (shared across transport, freight, warehouse).
- **Back link:** `PageBackLinkComponent` without `[form]` (read-only)
- **Actions:** `DetailActionBarComponent` in `[detailFooterActions]` below the details card — right-aligned; Edit/Delete (own) or Send request (marketplace)

## Page template

Use **separate `@if` blocks** per projected slot — Angular control flow breaks multi-node projection (NG8011).

```html
<app-detail-page-layout entityTab="transport">
  <app-page-back-link detailBack [route]="back().url" [labelKey]="back().labelKey" />
  <app-page-title
    [titleKey]="pageTitleKey"
    [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey()"
    [icon]="pageIcon"
    entityTab="transport"
  />

  @if (loading()) {
    <section detailContent class="detail-page-card detail-page-card--loading">…</section>
  } @else if (entity(); as row) {
    <app-entity-detail-summary detailSummary kind="route" [status]="row.status" [origin]="row.origin" [destination]="row.destination" />
  }

  @if (!loading() && entity(); as row) {
    <section detailContent class="detail-page-card">
      <app-detail-view [definition]="TransportDetail" [data]="row" />
    </section>
  }

  @if (!loading() && entity()) {
    <app-detail-action-bar detailFooterActions [actions]="detailActions()" layout="inline" (action)="onDetailAction($event)" />
  }
</app-detail-page-layout>
```

Warehouse: `kind="warehouse"` + `[warehouseName]` + `[warehouseCity]`.

Shared card styles: `styles/_detail-page.scss` (`.detail-page-card`).

**Entity card accent:** pass matching `entityTab` on `app-page-title` and `app-detail-page-layout`. Summary band gets left + top; `.detail-page-card` below gets left spine only. See `entity-service-colors.mdc`.

## Actions

`buildDetailPageActions(entityKind, { isOwnListing, editRoute })`:

| Scope | Actions |
|-------|---------|
| External (marketplace) | Send request (primary) |
| Own (my listings) | Edit (primary link) + Delete (danger) |

Handle `sendRequest` / `delete` in page TS with `ConfirmService`; edit uses `route` on action def.

## Detail definition sections (current)

| Entity | Sections | Excluded from card (in summary) |
|--------|----------|----------------------------------|
| Transport | Schedule (dates), Vehicle & description (vehicle, description) | status, route |
| Freight | Shipment (type, size, weight, dates, description) | status, route |
| Warehouse | Availability (dates, space), Details (description) | status, warehouse |

## Table row click

`DataTableComponent`: `[rowClickEnabled]="true"` + `(rowClick)="onRowClick($event)"`. Row actions menu stops propagation.

## i18n

| Path | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `portal.user.pages.viewTransport\|viewFreight\|viewWarehouse.title` | Page title |
| `portal.user.pages.listingDetail.subtitleSearch` | Another company's listing (all entities) |
| `portal.user.pages.listingDetail.subtitleOur` | Your company's listing (all entities) |
| `portal.user.features.<entity>.detail.sections.*` | Section headings in DetailView |

